<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861216-0083 </DOCNO><HL> Rockwell's Allen-BradleyAcquires Over 90% of Firm</HL><DD> 12/16/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ROKTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> MILWAUKEE  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Allen-Bradley Co. said it purchased more than 90% of DataMyte Corp. and intends to merge DataMyte into a subsidiary by year's end.    Details of the acquisition weren't disclosed.    Allen-Bradley, a subsidiary of Rockwell International Corp. of Pittsburgh, said it acquired more than 90% of closely held DataMyte's four million shares outstanding and will complete the acquisition of the Minnetonka, Minn., company by the end of the year. DataMyte will operate as part of Allen-Bradley's industrial systems and parts group, in Milwaukee.    Allen-Bradley is a maker of industrial automation control and communications systems. DataMyte makes monitoring systems for automation controls. </TEXT></DOC>